# Cloudinary Patterns

## DB convention
- Store `public_id` in `cover_url` and in `gallery` jsonb, NEVER full URLs.
- Format: `sofi-mosquera/projects/{slug}/01` or `sofi-mosquera/artworks/{slug}/cover`.
- The `cldUrl()` helper handles both public_ids AND full URLs (backward compat).

## Import helpers from @sofi/ui
- `cldUrl(publicId, opts)` — flexible builder
- `cldThumb(publicId)` — 600x750 fill
- `cldCard(publicId)` — 800x1000 fill (4:5 for cards)
- `cldHero(publicId)` — 2000x1200 fill (wide hero)
- `cldSquare(publicId)` — 600x600 fill
- `cldArtwork(publicId)` — 900x1200 fit (preserves aspect)
- `cldGallery(publicId)` — 1600x1000 fill (detail gallery)
- `cldZoom(publicId)` — 2400px limit, q:90 (lightbox)

## Usage in components
```tsx
import { cldCard } from "@sofi/ui";

<img src={cldCard(project.coverUrl)} alt={project.title} loading="lazy" />
```

## Upload workflow
- Bulk from filesystem: `npx tsx scripts/upload-images.ts` (reads `assets/` folder)
- Ongoing from admin UI: use `<CloudinaryUpload>` component (signed via `/api/cloudinary-sign`)
- Max 10MB per file on free tier — compress large files first
